::: {.callout-warning}
## Event coding in the bundled data

Several of these datasets follow R's convention rather than the `0`/`1` convention for the
status column. `lung` codes status as `1` = censored and `2` = dead. `pbc` uses three levels
(`0` / `1` / `2`). Always inspect the column and convert it explicitly when building the
response. See [Survival data](survival-data.qmd) for why Greenwood does not guess at event
coding.
:::

